quran[564]{c,v,t}:
  78,1,About what do they question one another
  78,2,About the Great Tiding
  78,3,regarding which they differ
  78,4,"Nay, but they will know"
  78,5,Then indeed they will know
  78,6,Did We not make the earth a resting place
  78,7,and the mountains stakes
  78,8,and create you in pairs
  78,9,and make your sleep repose
  78,10,and make the night a garment
  78,11,and the day for livelihood
  78,12,"And [did We not] build above you seven firmaments"
  78,13,and make a radiant lamp
  78,14,and send down water pouring from the rain clouds
  78,15,that We might produce grain and plants thereby
  78,16,and luxuriant gardens
  78,17,Truly the Day of Division is a Moment Appointed
  78,18,a day when the trumpet is blown and you come forth in throngs
  78,19,and the sky is opened as if it were gates
  78,20,and the mountains are set in motion as if they were a mirage
  78,21,Truly Hell lies in ambush
  78,22,a place unto which the rebellious return
  78,23,to tarry therein for ages
  78,24,They taste therein neither coolness nor drink
  78,25,"save boiling liquid and a cold, murky fluid"
  78,26,a fitting recompense
  78,27,Truly they anticipated not a reckoning
  78,28,and denied Our signs with utter denial
  78,29,And everything have We recorded in a book
  78,30,So taste! For We shall not increase you in aught but punishment
  78,31,Truly the reverent shall have a place of triumph
  78,32,gardens and vineyards
  78,33,buxom maidens of like age
  78,34,and an overflowing cup
  78,35,They hear therein neither idle talk nor lying—
  78,36,"a recompense from thy Lord, a gift abounding—"
  78,37,"the Lord of the heavens and the earth, and whatsoever is between them, the Compassionate, Whom they have no power to address"
  78,38,"That Day the Spirit and the angels stand in rows, none speaking, save one whom the Compassionate permits and who speaks aright"
  78,39,"That is the True Day. So let whosoever will, take a path of return unto his Lord"
  78,40,"Truly We have warned you of a punishment nigh, on a day when a man beholds what his hands have sent forth, and the disbeliever says, “Oh, would that I were dust!”"
  79,1,By those that wrest violently
  79,2,by those that draw out quickly
  79,3,by those that glide serenely
  79,4,"by those that race to the fore, outstripping"
  79,5,and by those that govern affairs
  79,6,on the Day when the quaker quakes
  79,7,and the successor follows upon it
  79,8,Hearts that Day shall tremble
  79,9,with eyes humbled
  79,10,"They will say, “Are we to be restored as we were before"
  79,11,What! When we have become decayed bones?”
  79,12,"They say, “This, then, would be a ruinous return!”"
  79,13,Yet it shall be but a single cry
  79,14,"then, behold, they will be upon a wide expanse"
  79,15,Hast thou heard tell of Moses
  79,16,when his Lord called out to him in the holy valley of ?uwa
  79,17,“Go unto Pharaoh! Truly he has rebelled
  79,18,"And say, ‘Dost thou wish to be purified"
  79,19,and that I guide thee to thy Lord that thou mightest have fear?’”
  79,20,Then he showed him the greatest sign
  79,21,But he denied and disobeyed
  79,22,"Then turned his back, moving swiftly"
  79,23,Then he gathered and proclaimed
  79,24,"and said, “I am your lord most high.”"
  79,25,So God seized him with a punishment exemplary in the Hereafter and in this world
  79,26,Truly in that is a lesson for whosoever fears
  79,27,Are you more difficult to create or the sky that He has built
  79,28,He raised high its canopy and fashioned it
  79,29,"darkened its night, and brought forth its day"
  79,30,And after that He spread out the earth
  79,31,From it He brought forth its water and its pastures
  79,32,and the mountains He set firm
  79,33,as sustenance for you and for your flocks
  79,34,So when the Great Calamity befalls—
  79,35,a day when man shall remember that for which he endeavored
  79,36,and Hellfire is made visible for one who sees—
  79,37,as for one who rebels
  79,38,and prefers the life of this world
  79,39,truly Hellfire is the refuge
  79,40,As for one who fears standing before his Lord and forbids the soul from caprice
  79,41,truly the Garden is the refuge
  79,42,"They ask thee about the Hour, “When shall it set in?”"
  79,43,What hast thou to do with mentioning it
  79,44,"Unto thy Lord is [knowledge of] the end thereof"
  79,45,Thou art but a warner for whosoever fears it
  79,46,"The Day they see it, it will be as if they had tarried but an evening or the morning thereof"
  80,1,He frowned and turned away
  80,2,because the blind man came to him
  80,3,And what would apprise thee? Perhaps he would purify himself
  80,4,"or be reminded, such that the reminder might benefit him"
  80,5,As for him who deems himself beyond need
  80,6,to him dost thou attend
  80,7,"though thou art not answerable, should he not be purified"
  80,8,But as for him who came to thee striving earnestly
  80,9,while fearful
  80,10,from him thou art diverted
  80,11,Nay! Truly it is a reminder—
  80,12,"so let whomsoever will, remember it—"
  80,13,on pages honored
  80,14,exalted and purified
  80,15,in the hands of scribes
  80,16,noble and pious
  80,17,May man perish! How ungrateful is he
  80,18,From what thing did He create him
  80,19,"From a drop He created him, then proportioned him"
  80,20,then He made the way easy for him
  80,21,Then He caused him to die and buried him
  80,22,"Then, when He willed, He resurrected him"
  80,23,Nay! But he has not accomplished what He commanded him
  80,24,So let man consider his food
  80,25,that We pour down water in abundance
  80,26,then We split the earth in fissures
  80,27,and cause grains to grow therein
  80,28,and vines and herbs
  80,29,and olives and date palms
  80,30,and gardens densely planted
  80,31,and fruit and pastures
  80,32,as sustenance for you and for your flocks
  80,33,So when the Piercing Cry does come
  80,34,that Day when a man will flee from his brother
  80,35,and his mother and his father
  80,36,and his spouse and his children
  80,37,For every man that Day his affair shall suffice him
  80,38,"Faces that Day shall be shining, radiant"
  80,39,"laughing, joyous"
  80,40,And faces that Day shall be covered with dust
  80,41,overspread with darkness
  80,42,"Those, they are the disbelievers, the profligates"
  81,1,When the sun is enfolded
  81,2,and when the stars fade away
  81,3,when the mountains are set in motion
  81,4,and when pregnant camels are abandoned
  81,5,when the wild beasts are gathered
  81,6,and when the seas are made to swell over
  81,7,when the souls are coupled
  81,8,and when the female infant buried alive is asked
  81,9,for what sin she was slain
  81,10,when the pages are spread
  81,11,and when Heaven is laid bare
  81,12,when Hellfire is kindled
  81,13,and when the Garden is brought nigh
  81,14,each soul shall know what it has made ready
  81,15,So I swear by those receding
  81,16,those that move and set
  81,17,by the night as it approaches
  81,18,and by the morning as it breathes
  81,19,Truly it is the speech of a noble messenger
  81,20,"possessed of strength, before the Possessor of the Throne, of high rank"
  81,21,"obeyed, trustworthy withal"
  81,22,Your companion is not possessed
  81,23,He surely saw him upon the clear horizon
  81,24,And he does not withhold grudgingly the Unseen
  81,25,Nor is it the speech of a satan outcast
  81,26,So where are you going
  81,27,It is naught but a reminder for the worlds
  81,28,for those of you who will to go straight
  81,29,"And you do not will but that God, Lord of the worlds, wills"
  82,1,When the sky is cleft asunder
  82,2,and when the stars are dispersed
  82,3,when the seas are burst forth
  82,4,and when graves are turned inside out
  82,5,then shall each soul know what it has sent forth and what it has left behind. j
  82,6,O mankind! What has deluded you with regard to your noble Lord
  82,7,"Who created you, then fashioned you, then proportioned you"
  82,8,assembling you in whatever form He willed
  82,9,Nay! But you deny religion
  82,10,And yet truly over you there are guardians
  82,11,"noble, writing"
  82,12,knowing what you do
  82,13,Truly the pious shall be in bliss
  82,14,and truly the profligate shall be in Hellfire
  82,15,burning therein on the Day of Judgment
  82,16,And they will not be absent from it
  82,17,And what will apprise thee of the Day of Judgment
  82,18,Then what will apprise thee of the Day of Judgment
  82,19,"A day when no soul will avail another soul in any way, and the Command that Day is with God"
  83,1,Woe unto the defrauders
  83,2,"who, when they take measure from people, demand [it] in full"
  83,3,"and when they measure for them or weigh for them, they stint"
  83,4,Do they not think that they will be resurrected
  83,5,unto a tremendous day—
  83,6,a day when mankind shall stand before the Lord of the worlds
  83,7,Nay! Truly the book of the profligate is in Sijjin
  83,8,And what will apprise thee of Sijjin
  83,9,A book inscribed
  83,10,Woe that Day to the deniers
  83,11,who deny the Day of Judgment
  83,12,which none deny save every sinful transgressor
  83,13,"When Our signs are recited unto him, he says, “Fables of those of old!”"
  83,14,Nay! But that which they used to earn has covered their hearts with rust
  83,15,Nay! Surely on that Day they will be veiled from their Lord
  83,16,Then they will burn in Hellfire
  83,17,"Then it is said unto them, “This is that which you used to deny.”"
  83,18,"Nay, truly the book of the pious is in ?Illiyyun"
  83,19,And what will apprise thee of ?Illiyyun
  83,20,A book inscribed
  83,21,witnessed by those brought nigh
  83,22,Truly the pious shall be in bliss
  83,23,"upon couches, gazing"
  83,24,Thou dost recognize in their faces the splendor of bliss
  83,25,They are given to drink of pure wine sealed
  83,26,whose seal is musk—so for that let the strivers strive—
  83,27,and whose mixture is of Tasnim
  83,28,a spring whence drink those brought nigh
  83,29,Truly those who sinned did laugh at those who believed
  83,30,"When they passed them, they would wink at one another"
  83,31,"And when they returned to their people, they would return blithely"
  83,32,"And when they saw them, they said, “Truly these are astray!”"
  83,33,Though they were not sent as guardians over them
  83,34,So that Day those who believe shall laugh at those who disbelieve
  83,35,"upon couches, gazing"
  83,36,Have the disbelievers been requited for that which they used to do
  84,1,When the sky is rent asunder
  84,2,"and hearkens unto its Lord, as in truth it must"
  84,3,and when the earth is stretched out
  84,4,"and casts forth what is in it, emptying itself"
  84,5,"and hearkens unto its Lord, as in truth it must. j"
  84,6,"O mankind! Truly thou art laboring unto thy Lord laboriously, and shall meet Him"
  84,7,As for one who is given his book in his right hand
  84,8,he will be reckoned with an easy reckoning
  84,9,and will return to his people joyful
  84,10,But as for one who is given his book from behind his back
  84,11,he will cry out for destruction
  84,12,and will enter a Blaze
  84,13,Truly among his people he was joyful
  84,14,Truly he thought that he would never return
  84,15,Nay! Truly his Lord was watchful of him
  84,16,So I swear by the twilight
  84,17,by the night and what it enshrouds
  84,18,and by the moon when full
  84,19,thou wilt surely journey from stage to stage
  84,20,So what ails them that they believe not
  84,21,"and that when the Quran is recited unto them, they do not prostrate"
  84,22,Nay! Those who disbelieve deny
  84,23,But God knows best what they conceal
  84,24,So give them glad tidings of a painful punishment
  84,25,save those who believe and perform righteous deeds; theirs shall be a reward unceasing
  85,1,By the sky possessed of constellations
  85,2,By the Day promised
  85,3,and by the witness and the witnessed
  85,4,"May they perish, the inhabitants of the pit"
  85,5,the fire well fueled
  85,6,when they sat by it
  85,7,and were witness to what they did unto the believers
  85,8,"and took vengeance on them for naught but that they believed in God, the Mighty, the Praised"
  85,9,unto Whom belongs sovereignty over the heavens and the earth; and God is Witness over all things
  85,10,"Truly those who persecute believing men and believing women, then do not repent, theirs shall be the punishment of Hell, and theirs shall be the punishment of the burning"
  85,11,"Truly those who believe and perform righteous deeds, theirs shall be Gardens with rivers running below: that is the supreme triumph"
  85,12,Truly thy Lord’s assault is severe
  85,13,Truly it is He Who originates and brings back
  85,14,"And He is the Forgiving, the Loving"
  85,15,"Possessor of the Throne, the Glorious"
  85,16,Doer of whatsoever He will
  85,17,Hast thou heard tell of the hosts—
  85,18,Pharaoh and Thamud
  85,19,Yet those who disbelieve are in denial
  85,20,"And God is behind them, All-Encompassing"
  85,21,"Nay, it is a glorious Quran"
  85,22,upon a Preserved Tablet
  86,1,By the sky and that which comes by night
  86,2,And what will apprise thee of that which comes by night
  86,3,It is the piercing star
  86,4,Over every soul there is a guardian
  86,5,So let man consider that from which he was created
  86,6,He was created from a gushing fluid
  86,7,issuing from between the loins and the pelvic arch
  86,8,Truly He is able to bring him back
  86,9,on the Day when secrets are tested
  86,10,whereat man has neither strength nor helper
  86,11,By the resurgent sky
  86,12,and by the furrowed earth
  86,13,truly it is indeed a decisive Word
  86,14,And it is not for amusement
  86,15,Truly they are devising a scheme
  86,16,"and I, too, am devising a scheme"
  86,17,So be gentle with the disbelievers; grant them respite for a while
  87,1,"Glorify the Name of thy Lord, the Most High"
  87,2,"Who created, then fashioned"
  87,3,"Who measured out, then guided"
  87,4,and Who brought forth pasture
  87,5,then made it as blackened stubble
  87,6,"We shall teach thee to recite, that thou wilt not forget"
  87,7,save what God wills. Truly He knows that which is open and that which is hidden
  87,8,And We shall ease thy way unto ease
  87,9,"So remind, should the reminder benefit"
  87,10,he who fears will remember
  87,11,while the most wretched shall avoid it
  87,12,he who enters into the greatest Fire
  87,13,then neither dies therein nor lives
  87,14,He indeed prospers who is purified
  87,15,remembers the Name of his Lord and prays
  87,16,"Nay, but you prefer the life of this world"
  87,17,while the Hereafter is better and more enduring
  87,18,Truly this is in the scriptures of old
  87,19,the scriptures of Abraham and Moses
  88,1,Hast thou heard tell of the overwhelming event
  88,2,Faces that Day shall be humbled
  88,3,"toiling, weary"
  88,4,entering a scorching Fire
  88,5,given drink from a boiling spring
  88,6,"They will have no food, save a vile thorn"
  88,7,which neither nourishes nor avails against hunger
  88,8,Faces that Day shall be blessed
  88,9,contented by their endeavoring
  88,10,in a lofty Garden
  88,11,wherein they hear no idle talk
  88,12,Therein lies a flowing spring
  88,13,therein are raised couches
  88,14,goblets placed
  88,15,cushions arrayed
  88,16,and carpets spread
  88,17,"Do they not consider the camels, how they are created"
  88,18,"the sky, how it is raised"
  88,19,"the mountains, how they are established"
  88,20,"and the earth, how it is spread"
  88,21,So remind! Thou art but a reminder
  88,22,thou art not a warder over them
  88,23,But whosoever turns away and disbelieves
  88,24,God shall punish him with the greatest punishment
  88,25,Truly unto Us is their return
  88,26,then truly with Us lies their reckoning
  89,1,By the dawn
  89,2,by the ten nights
  89,3,by the even and the odd
  89,4,and by the night as it recedes
  89,5,is there an oath therein for one who is mindful
  89,6,Hast thou not seen how thy Lord dealt with ?Ad
  89,7,Iram the pillared
  89,8,the like of which was never created in all the land
  89,9,Thamud who hollowed the rocks in the valley
  89,10,and Pharaoh of the tent poles
  89,11,who tyrannized the land
  89,12,and increased corruption therein
  89,13,So thy Lord poured upon them the scourge of punishment
  89,14,Truly thy Lord lies in ambush
  89,15,"As for man, whenever his Lord tests him, then honors him and blesses him, he says, “My Lord has honored me.”"
  89,16,"And as for whenever He tries him and straitens his provision, he says, “My Lord has abased me.”"
  89,17,"Nay, but you honor not the orphan"
  89,18,nor urge you the feeding of the indigent
  89,19,You devour inheritance with rapacious devouring
  89,20,and love wealth with abounding love
  89,21,"Nay, but when the earth is ground up, grinding upon grinding"
  89,22,"and your Lord comes with the angels, row upon row"
  89,23,and Hell is brought forth that Day; that Day man will remember; yet whence will that remembrance avail him
  89,24,"He will say, “Would that I had sent forth for my life!”"
  89,25,That Day none punishes as He punishes
  89,26,and none binds as He binds
  89,27,O thou soul at peace
  89,28,"Return unto thy Lord, content, contenting"
  89,29,Enter among My servants
  89,30,Enter My Garden
  90,1,"Nay, I swear by this land"
  90,2,while thou art free in this land
  90,3,"and [by] the begetter, and that which he begat"
  90,4,truly We created man in travail
  90,5,Does he suppose that none will ever have power over him
  90,6,"He says, “I have squandered vast wealth!”"
  90,7,Does he suppose that no one sees him
  90,8,Did We not make for him two eyes
  90,9,"a tongue, and two lips"
  90,10,and guide him upon the two highways
  90,11,Yet he has not assailed the steep pass
  90,12,And what will apprise thee of the steep pass
  90,13,"[It is] the freeing of a slave"
  90,14,or giving food at a time of famine
  90,15,to an orphan near of kin
  90,16,"or an indigent, clinging to the dust"
  90,17,"while being one of those who believe and exhort one another to patience, and exhort one another to compassion"
  90,18,Those are the companions of the right
  90,19,"And those who disbelieve in Our signs, they are the companions of the left"
  90,20,Upon them is a Fire enclosed
  91,1,By the sun and its morning brightness
  91,2,by the moon when following it
  91,3,by the day when disclosing it
  91,4,by the night when enshrouding it
  91,5,by the sky and the One Who established it
  91,6,by the earth and the One Who spread it
  91,7,by the soul and the One Who fashioned it
  91,8,and inspired it as to what makes it iniquitous or reverent
  91,9,"Indeed, he prospers who purifies it"
  91,10,And indeed he fails who obscures it
  91,11,Thamud denied in their rebelliousness
  91,12,when the most wretched of them was dispatched
  91,13,"So the messenger of God said to them, “[This is] the she-camel of God; give her drink!”"
  91,14,"But they denied him, then hamstrung her. So their Lord crushed them for their sin, then leveled it"
  91,15,for He fears not the consequence thereof
  92,1,By the night as it enshrouds
  92,2,by the day as it discloses
  92,3,by Him Who created the male and the female
  92,4,truly your endeavors are diverse
  92,5,As for one who gives and is reverent
  92,6,and attests to what is most beautiful
  92,7,We shall ease his way unto ease
  92,8,And as for one who is miserly and deems himself beyond need
  92,9,and denies what is most beautiful
  92,10,We shall ease his way unto hardship
  92,11,and his wealth shall not avail him when he perishes
  92,12,Truly Ours it is to give guidance
  92,13,and truly unto Us belong the Hereafter and this world
  92,14,Thus have I warned you of a raging Fire
  92,15,"which none shall enter, save the most wretched"
  92,16,who denies and turns away
  92,17,And the most reverent shall be removed from it
  92,18,who gives his wealth to purify
  92,19,not recompensing any for a favor thereby
  92,20,"save for seeking the Face of his Lord, the Most High"
  92,21,and surely he shall be content
  93,1,By the morning brightness
  93,2,and by the night when still
  93,3,thy Lord has not forsaken thee; nor does He despise
  93,4,And the Hereafter shall be better for thee than this life
  93,5,"And surely thy Lord shall give unto thee, and thou shalt be content"
  93,6,Did He not find thee an orphan and shelter
  93,7,find thee astray and guide
  93,8,and find thee in need and enrich
  93,9,"So as for the orphan, scorn not"
  93,10,"And as for one who requests, repel not"
  93,11,"And as for the blessing of thy Lord, proclaim"
  94,1,Did We not expand for thee thy breast
  94,2,and lift from thee thy burden
  94,3,that weighed heavily upon thy back
  94,4,And did We not elevate thy renown
  94,5,For truly with hardship comes ease
  94,6,Truly with hardship comes ease
  94,7,"So when thou art free, exert thyself"
  94,8,and let thy desire be for thy Lord
  95,1,By the fig and the olive
  95,2,by Mount Sinai
  95,3,and by this land made safe
  95,4,truly We created man in the most beautiful stature
  95,5,then We cast him to the lowest of the low
  95,6,save those who believe and perform righteous deeds; for theirs shall be a reward unceasing
  95,7,What then will make you deny religion
  95,8,Is not God the most just of judges
  96,1,Recite in the Name of thy Lord Who created
  96,2,created man from a blood clot
  96,3,Recite! Thy Lord is most noble
  96,4,Who taught by the Pen
  96,5,taught man that which he knew not
  96,6,"Nay, truly man is rebellious"
  96,7,in that he considers himself beyond need
  96,8,Truly unto thy Lord is the return
  96,9,Hast thou seen him who prohibits
  96,10,a slave when he prays
  96,11,Hast thou seen if he does so out of guidance
  96,12,or to enjoin reverence
  96,13,Hast thou seen if he denied and turned away
  96,14,Does he not know that God sees
  96,15,"Nay, but if he ceases not, We shall surely seize him by the forelock—"
  96,16,"a lying, iniquitous forelock"
  96,17,So let him call his cohorts
  96,18,We shall call the guards of Hell
  96,19,Nay! Obey him not! But prostrate and draw nigh
  97,1,Truly We sent it down in the Night of Power
  97,2,And what shall apprise thee of the Night of Power
  97,3,The Night of Power is better than a thousand months
  97,4,"The angels and the Spirit descend therein, by the leave of their Lord, with every command"
  97,5,peace it is until the break of dawn
  98,1,Those who disbelieve among the People of the Book and the idolaters will not desist until the clear proof comes unto them
  98,2,a messenger from God reciting scriptures purified
  98,3,wherein are books upright
  98,4,Those who were given the Book did not become divided until after the clear proof had come unto them
  98,5,"They were not commanded but to worship God, devoting religion entirely to Him, as ?anifs, and to perform the prayer, and to give the alms—that is the upright religion"
  98,6,"Truly the disbelievers among the People of the Book and the idolaters are in the Fire of Hell, abiding therein; it is they who are the worst of creation"
  98,7,"Truly those who believe and perform righteous deeds, it is they who are the best of creation"
  98,8,"Their reward is with their Lord, Gardens of Eden with rivers running below, abiding therein forever, God being content with them and they being content with Him. That is for whosoever fears his Lord"
  99,1,When the earth is shaken with her shaking
  99,2,and the earth yields up her burdens
  99,3,"and man says, “What ails her?”"
  99,4,That Day she shall convey her chronicles
  99,5,for thy Lord inspired her
  99,6,That Day mankind shall issue forth upon diverse paths to witness their deeds
  99,7,So whosoever does a mote’s weight of good shall see it
  99,8,And whosoever does a mote’s weight of evil shall see it
  100,1,By the panting chargers
  100,2,by the strikers of sparks
  100,3,by the raiders at dawn
  100,4,raising thereby a trail of dust
  100,5,penetrating to the center altogether
  100,6,truly man is ungrateful to his Lord
  100,7,and truly he is a witness to that
  100,8,and truly he is fierce in his love for good things
  100,9,Does he not know that when what lies within graves is turned inside out
  100,10,and what lies within breasts is made known
  100,11,truly on that Day their Lord shall be aware of them
  101,1,The calamity
  101,2,what is the calamity
  101,3,And what shall apprise thee of the calamity
  101,4,A day wherein mankind shall be like scattered moths
  101,5,and the mountains shall be like carded wool
  101,6,As for one whose scales are heavy
  101,7,he shall enjoy a life contenting
  101,8,And as for one whose scales are light
  101,9,an abyss shall be his mother
  101,10,And what shall apprise thee of her
  101,11,It is a raging fire
  102,1,Vying for increase distracts you
  102,2,till you visit the graves
  102,3,Nay! Soon you will know
  102,4,Indeed! Soon you will know
  102,5,Nay! If you knew with the knowledge of certainty
  102,6,you would surely see Hellfire
  102,7,Then you would surely see it with the eye of certainty
  102,8,Then surely you will be questioned that Day about the blessing
  103,1,By the declining day
  103,2,truly mankind is in loss
  103,3,"save those who believe, perform righteous deeds, exhort one another to truth, and exhort one another to patience"
  104,1,Woe unto every slandering backbiter
  104,2,who amasses wealth and tallies it
  104,3,supposing that his wealth makes him immortal
  104,4,Nay! He shall surely be cast into the crushing Fire
  104,5,And what shall apprise thee of the crushing Fire
  104,6,"The Fire of God, ignited"
  104,7,which engulfs hearts
  104,8,Truly it is enclosed upon them
  104,9,in pillars outstretched
  105,1,Hast thou not seen how thy Lord dealt with the masters of the elephant
  105,2,Did He not make their scheming go astray
  105,3,and send against them birds in swarms
  105,4,pelting them with stones of baked clay
  105,5,such that He made them like devoured husks
  106,1,For the secure passage of the Quraysh
  106,2,their secure passage in the journey of winter and of summer
  106,3,so let them worship the Lord of this house
  106,4,Who relieved them of hunger and made them safe from fear
  107,1,Hast thou seen the one who denies religion
  107,2,That is the one who drives away the orphan
  107,3,and does not urge feeding the indigent
  107,4,So woe unto the praying
  107,5,who are heedless of their prayers
  107,6,those who strive to be seen
  107,7,yet refuse small kindnesses
  108,1,Truly We have bestowed abundant good upon thee
  108,2,So pray to thy Lord and sacrifice
  108,3,Truly thine enemy shall be the one without posterity
  109,1,"Say, “O disbelievers"
  109,2,I worship not what you worship
  109,3,nor are you worshippers of what I worship
  109,4,nor am I a worshipper of what you worship
  109,5,nor are you worshippers of what I worship
  109,6,"Unto you your religion, and unto me my religion.”"
  110,1,When God’s Help and Victory come
  110,2,and you see mankind entering God’s religion in throngs
  110,3,"hymn the praise of thy Lord, and seek forgiveness from Him. Truly He is Ever Relenting"
  111,1,"May the hands of Abu Lahab perish, and may he perish"
  111,2,"His wealth avails him not, nor what he has earned"
  111,3,He shall enter a blazing Fire
  111,4,"And his wife, carrier of firewood"
  111,5,upon her neck is a rope of palm fiber
  112,1,"Say, “He, God, is One"
  112,2,"God, the Eternally Sufficient unto Himself"
  112,3,He begets not; nor was He begotten
  112,4,And none is like unto Him.”
  113,1,"Say, “I seek refuge in the Lord of the daybreak"
  113,2,from the evil of what He has created
  113,3,from the evil of darkness when it enshrouds
  113,4,from the evil of those who blow upon knots
  113,5,and from the evil of the envier when he envies.”
  114,1,"Say, “I seek refuge in the Lord of mankind"
  114,2,the King of mankind
  114,3,the God of mankind
  114,4,from the evil of the stealthy whisperer
  114,5,who whispers into the breasts of mankind
  114,6,from jinn and mankind.”